1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:02:00,000
(Watch on www.dramacool.club Support Admin)

2
00:03:30,581 --> 00:03:32,374
You're finally awake.

3
00:03:33,696 --> 00:03:34,697
Maggie?

4
00:03:42,718 --> 00:03:44,362
Hey! Are you okay?

5
00:03:44,386 --> 00:03:45,906
The person behind your abduction

6
00:03:45,930 --> 00:03:48,909
is someone who reeks of evil
and relentless manipulation.

7
00:03:48,933 --> 00:03:52,037
Welcome to the White Hostel!

8
00:03:52,061 --> 00:03:56,398
You think, you can already play
the role of Janine's boyfriend?

9
00:04:00,277 --> 00:04:02,150
I didn't mean to!

10
00:04:04,532 --> 00:04:05,866
I let myself in.

11
00:04:07,326 --> 00:04:08,369
I hope you don't mind.

12
00:04:09,954 --> 00:04:11,080
My name is Luthor...

13
00:04:11,705 --> 00:04:12,705
Mendez.

14
00:04:12,961 --> 00:04:14,337
Loki's elder brother.

15
00:04:33,018 --> 00:04:36,313
It seems like your club
is busy attending to new clients.

16
00:04:39,942 --> 00:04:41,360
I let myself in.

17
00:04:48,534 --> 00:04:49,952
That's enough, Maggie!

18
00:04:52,663 --> 00:04:54,039
I hope you don't mind.

19
00:04:55,416 --> 00:04:56,518
Forgive my manners.

20
00:04:56,542 --> 00:04:58,460
I haven't introduced myself properly.

21
00:04:59,211 --> 00:05:00,421
My name is Luthor...

22
00:05:00,963 --> 00:05:01,991
Mendez.

23
00:05:02,381 --> 00:05:03,799
Loki's elder brother.

24
00:05:11,891 --> 00:05:12,933
Luthor.

25
00:05:13,559 --> 00:05:14,768
Nice to meet you.

26
00:05:15,269 --> 00:05:16,478
I'm Lorelei.

27
00:05:18,564 --> 00:05:20,274
Nice to meet you, Lorelei.

28
00:05:33,329 --> 00:05:34,455
What the hell?

29
00:05:55,226 --> 00:05:57,144
Did you let this guy inside our clubroom?

30
00:05:57,436 --> 00:05:58,439
If not

31
00:05:58,771 --> 00:06:00,457
did he materialize out of thin air?

32
00:06:00,481 --> 00:06:02,000
Or did he emerge out of the pentagram?

33
00:06:02,024 --> 00:06:04,002
Look, look. I'm sorry. Okay?

34
00:06:04,026 --> 00:06:06,737
First of all,
I had no idea he was your brother.

35
00:06:06,904 --> 00:06:10,199
Secondly, I didn't know
that's how you'd react.

36
00:06:10,908 --> 00:06:12,368
Look, for all we know,

37
00:06:12,910 --> 00:06:14,387
he might bring up a case.

38
00:06:14,411 --> 00:06:15,411
Case?

39
00:06:15,913 --> 00:06:17,098
Turns out there's a case

40
00:06:17,122 --> 00:06:19,041
even a master manipulator like you
can't handle.

41
00:06:20,167 --> 00:06:23,963
With all those resources
and schemes up your sleeve?

42
00:06:25,214 --> 00:06:26,382
You disappoint me.

43
00:06:27,341 --> 00:06:29,510
I'm just preoccupied with other things.

44
00:06:30,094 --> 00:06:31,094
Besides

45
00:06:31,929 --> 00:06:35,182
the problem that I will refer to you
requires an outsider's hand.

46
00:06:37,184 --> 00:06:39,311
We don't accept suspicious requests.

47
00:06:40,104 --> 00:06:41,272
So leave.

48
00:06:43,983 --> 00:06:46,544
Did you forget
that I'm the chairman of the committee

49
00:06:46,568 --> 00:06:48,320
of non-mandated organizations?

50
00:06:49,530 --> 00:06:53,885
Even if you haven't met
the minimum number of members,

51
00:06:53,909 --> 00:06:55,577
your renewal still got approved.

52
00:06:56,870 --> 00:07:00,833
So, yeah, I would expect for you
to show a little bit of gratitude

53
00:07:01,250 --> 00:07:02,584
by doing us a favor.

54
00:07:03,877 --> 00:07:06,338
If you don't want,
it's easy to reverse the decision.

55
00:07:07,172 --> 00:07:09,727
The Paranormal Club seems to fit in here.

56
00:07:11,176 --> 00:07:13,887
You know they've been requesting
for this clubroom for ages.

57
00:07:14,596 --> 00:07:17,683
I told you before
that he's despicable, didn't I?

58
00:07:18,892 --> 00:07:21,579
So should we discuss my request

59
00:07:21,603 --> 00:07:24,606
or should I leave now
and revoke your club's status?

60
00:07:31,256 --> 00:07:33,158
♪ Shadows ♪

61
00:07:33,930 --> 00:07:36,641
♪ in the dark are crawling ♪

62
00:07:37,521 --> 00:07:40,076
♪ Keeping watch and barring your way ♪

63
00:07:40,134 --> 00:07:44,613
♪ As if the line could not be crossed ♪

64
00:07:45,600 --> 00:07:49,163
♪ To every scream and every tremor ♪

65
00:07:49,187 --> 00:07:52,333
♪ These walls remain the only witness ♪

66
00:07:52,357 --> 00:07:55,294
♪ Every noise is etched in here ♪

67
00:07:55,318 --> 00:07:59,823
♪ Like fire and ammunition
for your memory ♪

68
00:08:01,245 --> 00:08:03,372
♪ Heed the warnings ♪

69
00:08:04,837 --> 00:08:07,214
♪ The threats poised to strike ♪

70
00:08:08,293 --> 00:08:11,963
♪ For this world ♪

71
00:08:12,377 --> 00:08:14,981
♪ is not what you imagined ♪

72
00:08:15,005 --> 00:08:17,565
♪ Heed the warnings ♪

73
00:08:18,467 --> 00:08:20,594
♪ Open up your eyes ♪

74
00:08:21,887 --> 00:08:25,432
♪ For this world ♪

75
00:08:26,141 --> 00:08:28,685
♪ is not what you imagined ♪

76
00:08:28,959 --> 00:08:33,645
♪ Heed the warnings ♪

77
00:08:36,376 --> 00:08:38,045
This is a confidential matter.

78
00:08:38,337 --> 00:08:40,922
A friend of mine is being blackmailed
by another student.

79
00:08:41,120 --> 00:08:42,288
Is it really a friend?

80
00:08:43,431 --> 00:08:45,058
Or maybe one of your pawns?

81
00:08:45,785 --> 00:08:48,329
A student named Charles Meliton,

82
00:08:48,806 --> 00:08:51,183
he has compromising photographs
of my friend.

83
00:08:51,995 --> 00:08:53,394
And he won't release those,

84
00:08:53,418 --> 00:08:56,213
unless we pay him 3,000 pesos per photo.

85
00:08:56,939 --> 00:08:59,024
How did he get those photos?

86
00:08:59,191 --> 00:09:01,693
That's what we don't know.

87
00:09:01,718 --> 00:09:04,179
But we're hundred percent certain
that he has them.

88
00:09:05,380 --> 00:09:06,590
This is not the first time

89
00:09:06,615 --> 00:09:09,284
that Charles tried to extort money
from another student.

90
00:09:09,575 --> 00:09:12,661
We received multiple reports
telling the same story.

91
00:09:14,543 --> 00:09:17,254
I guess you could call him
a serial blackmailer.

92
00:09:18,209 --> 00:09:19,209
Loki

93
00:09:19,511 --> 00:09:21,430
I think we should take on this case.

94
00:09:21,879 --> 00:09:25,082
No one deserves to have
their compromising photos exposed

95
00:09:25,107 --> 00:09:26,483
without their consent.

96
00:09:30,668 --> 00:09:31,668
So

97
00:09:32,170 --> 00:09:33,338
what do you want us to do?

98
00:09:34,130 --> 00:09:37,383
Beg him to stop blackmailing
your so-called friend and other students?

99
00:09:38,676 --> 00:09:42,031
I want you to retrieve the storage device
containing the said photos

100
00:09:42,055 --> 00:09:44,933
along with everything
that he's got on the other students.

101
00:09:45,683 --> 00:09:47,685
That's where he gets his confidence.

102
00:09:48,019 --> 00:09:51,147
You take that away from him,
he'd lose leverage.

103
00:09:57,320 --> 00:10:00,406
Why can't you solve
this petty problem on your own?

104
00:10:01,115 --> 00:10:04,494
You have plenty of resources
as part of the student council.

105
00:10:04,869 --> 00:10:08,039
You're just wasting your time asking us.

106
00:10:09,082 --> 00:10:11,227
Because Charles knows every officer

107
00:10:11,251 --> 00:10:13,586
in the student council
and executive committee.

108
00:10:14,462 --> 00:10:17,048
His awareness of us
makes any move from our side,

109
00:10:17,507 --> 00:10:18,841
I guess, risky?

110
00:10:20,969 --> 00:10:22,780
If he finds out we're planning something,

111
00:10:22,804 --> 00:10:25,473
he might get triggered
and upload the files.

112
00:10:26,599 --> 00:10:28,101
That's why it has to be you.

113
00:10:28,643 --> 00:10:29,852
A third party

114
00:10:30,436 --> 00:10:33,064
who is not under
the influence of the council.

115
00:10:35,400 --> 00:10:37,860
I'll have someone bring you
the files that we have on Charles.

116
00:10:38,528 --> 00:10:40,363
I hope that you can come up with a plan

117
00:10:40,822 --> 00:10:43,032
to end his villainy by tomorrow.

118
00:10:43,825 --> 00:10:45,034
If you pull this off,

119
00:10:46,119 --> 00:10:47,328
consider us even.

120
00:10:53,668 --> 00:10:55,211
And as for you, Lorelei

121
00:10:55,795 --> 00:10:57,463
I'd like to get to know you better.

122
00:10:58,464 --> 00:11:00,717
Maybe we can have a chat
over tea sometime.

123
00:11:33,541 --> 00:11:35,251
Hey! What are you doing?

124
00:11:38,171 --> 00:11:39,171
Hello?

125
00:11:39,631 --> 00:11:41,299
Earth to Loki.

126
00:11:50,975 --> 00:11:52,602
Feels like I have no one to talk to.

127
00:12:02,987 --> 00:12:04,447
I'd rather sit here for now.

128
00:12:06,240 --> 00:12:07,784
But I need to get a new chair.

129
00:12:09,494 --> 00:12:11,539
I can still feel his eerie presence

130
00:12:12,288 --> 00:12:14,165
just by staring at that chair.

131
00:12:14,666 --> 00:12:17,293
Why are you that angry at your brother?

132
00:12:19,087 --> 00:12:20,087
Lorelei

133
00:12:20,421 --> 00:12:21,714
you'll never understand.

134
00:12:23,091 --> 00:12:24,634
He's not your brother.

135
00:12:26,511 --> 00:12:31,724
You never told me your brother
is actually the VP of the student council.

136
00:12:32,850 --> 00:12:33,851
Actually

137
00:12:34,769 --> 00:12:37,522
he's not just the Vice President
of the student council.

138
00:12:39,148 --> 00:12:41,859
He is the student council.

139
00:12:43,361 --> 00:12:45,321
The President is just a puppet.

140
00:12:47,323 --> 00:12:49,158
It's my brother pulling the strings.

141
00:12:51,160 --> 00:12:52,160
That's why

142
00:12:52,704 --> 00:12:54,956
if ever he invites you to a tea party

143
00:12:57,208 --> 00:12:58,501
decline his offer.

144
00:13:00,128 --> 00:13:01,921
Or ignore his invitation completely.

145
00:13:04,424 --> 00:13:05,551
Hello?

146
00:13:05,591 --> 00:13:07,009
Can we help you?

147
00:13:08,428 --> 00:13:09,512
That was weird.

148
00:13:13,641 --> 00:13:14,641
What's that?

149
00:13:19,731 --> 00:13:22,108
So this is what Charles Meliton
looks like.

150
00:13:22,556 --> 00:13:24,933
To be fair, he looks innocent.

151
00:13:25,294 --> 00:13:27,094
Looks like he wouldn't do
something like that.

152
00:13:28,908 --> 00:13:30,397
Like what they say,

153
00:13:31,844 --> 00:13:33,262
looks can be deceiving.

154
00:13:34,912 --> 00:13:38,050
Some wolves hide very well
in sheep's clothing.

155
00:13:50,845 --> 00:13:52,180
This is all we need.

156
00:13:53,681 --> 00:13:55,391
The rest can be disregarded.

157
00:14:04,317 --> 00:14:06,277
We have to time this perfectly.

158
00:14:07,153 --> 00:14:09,197
We can't just approach him

159
00:14:10,072 --> 00:14:11,365
while he has class.

160
00:14:12,366 --> 00:14:13,366
But

161
00:14:15,745 --> 00:14:18,915
it's too risky to ambush him
during his break.

162
00:14:27,298 --> 00:14:29,300
How about during his P.E. class?

163
00:14:31,260 --> 00:14:32,303
P.E. class.

164
00:14:32,762 --> 00:14:35,115
P.E. class is the best time to ambush him

165
00:14:35,139 --> 00:14:37,642
since he'll definitely be changing
in the locker room.

166
00:14:39,143 --> 00:14:40,311
Here's the plan.

167
00:14:41,103 --> 00:14:42,897
You're the one going in the locker room,

168
00:14:43,648 --> 00:14:46,317
and I'll be your lookout outside.

169
00:14:52,448 --> 00:14:54,408
Aren't you good at lock picking?

170
00:14:54,665 --> 00:14:56,918
Opening his locker should be easy for you.

171
00:16:07,398 --> 00:16:09,293
Shoot! Shoot! Shoot!
Why did I just do that?

172
00:16:09,317 --> 00:16:11,110
Oh, no, no, no. He's coming.

173
00:16:20,703 --> 00:16:21,787
Let's go.

174
00:16:23,623 --> 00:16:25,017
So, did you see anything?

175
00:16:25,041 --> 00:16:27,585
He wouldn't be leaving something
as important as that.

176
00:16:28,336 --> 00:16:29,795
Maybe it's in his pocket?

177
00:16:30,880 --> 00:16:32,173
I don't think so.

178
00:16:32,673 --> 00:16:36,093
He wouldn't keep that in his pocket
during P.E. class.

179
00:16:36,677 --> 00:16:38,095
If it's a flash drive,

180
00:16:38,429 --> 00:16:39,597
he might lose it.

181
00:16:40,222 --> 00:16:41,933
If it's an external hard drive,

182
00:16:42,391 --> 00:16:44,143
it would be inconvenient for him.

183
00:16:46,103 --> 00:16:47,480
But look what I've found

184
00:16:48,481 --> 00:16:49,607
in his bag.

185
00:16:54,946 --> 00:16:56,697
Did he know we'd do this,

186
00:16:57,114 --> 00:16:58,783
so he put that there?

187
00:17:00,076 --> 00:17:01,285
I don't think so.

188
00:17:02,411 --> 00:17:03,746
By the looks of it,

189
00:17:05,122 --> 00:17:06,624
the paper looks old.

190
00:17:07,500 --> 00:17:09,377
Seems like it's been there for a while.

191
00:17:10,503 --> 00:17:11,921
So, what do we do?

192
00:17:13,214 --> 00:17:14,715
What I'm wondering is,

193
00:17:15,341 --> 00:17:17,259
why didn't Charles bring his phone?

194
00:17:18,052 --> 00:17:19,804
How did you know that?

195
00:17:20,179 --> 00:17:21,931
I didn't see a phone in his bag.

196
00:17:22,890 --> 00:17:24,308
I've been observing him

197
00:17:24,684 --> 00:17:27,979
and I haven't seen him
take out his phone not even once.

198
00:17:30,189 --> 00:17:32,984
It's impossible that he doesn't have
his own phone nowadays.

199
00:17:33,526 --> 00:17:36,487
So, does that mean he left it at home?

200
00:17:37,947 --> 00:17:39,156
That's my theory.

201
00:17:39,323 --> 00:17:42,159
Okay. Well, so what's our plan?

202
00:17:42,576 --> 00:17:43,995
It's time for Plan B.

203
00:17:45,037 --> 00:17:46,872
Do you know where Carl lives?

204
00:17:47,123 --> 00:17:48,266
Charles!

205
00:17:48,290 --> 00:17:50,042
It's Charles, Loki.

206
00:17:51,794 --> 00:17:52,878
Charles.

207
00:17:55,423 --> 00:17:57,133
Well, I got this.

208
00:17:58,092 --> 00:17:59,093
Charles.

209
00:18:06,392 --> 00:18:09,186
Meet me at the White Hostel, 5 p.m.

210
00:18:45,272 --> 00:18:46,732
Yes, Ms. Rios?

211
00:18:47,805 --> 00:18:48,805
Ma'am,

212
00:18:49,393 --> 00:18:51,604
I think I'm feeling a bit dizzy.

213
00:18:53,856 --> 00:18:55,066
Are you okay?

214
00:18:56,192 --> 00:18:58,402
May I go to the clinic?

215
00:18:59,195 --> 00:19:01,739
Okay, Ms. Rios. You'll be excused.

216
00:19:02,740 --> 00:19:04,426
Lori, do you want me to come with you?

217
00:19:04,450 --> 00:19:05,951
No, I've got this.

218
00:19:06,408 --> 00:19:07,387
But you said...

219
00:19:07,411 --> 00:19:09,497
Rosetta, I've got this.

220
00:19:12,124 --> 00:19:13,876
I'm feeling really dizzy.

221
00:19:19,048 --> 00:19:22,819
Ma'am, I think I'm starting
to feel dizzy too.

222
00:19:22,843 --> 00:19:25,137
Ms. Rodriguez, take your seat.

223
00:19:33,312 --> 00:19:34,355
Loki.

224
00:19:34,814 --> 00:19:36,107
What took you so long?

225
00:19:36,357 --> 00:19:38,418
Did you forget that we were supposed
to meet at 5 p.m.?

226
00:19:38,442 --> 00:19:39,669
It's already 5:10.

227
00:19:39,693 --> 00:19:41,946
I just came from my Humanities class.

228
00:19:42,321 --> 00:19:43,781
I kind of just ran off.

229
00:19:44,423 --> 00:19:45,591
Humanities?

230
00:19:45,616 --> 00:19:46,934
That's just a minor subject.

231
00:19:47,284 --> 00:19:48,929
Why on earth would you prioritize a subject

232
00:19:48,953 --> 00:19:51,223
that probably won't even matter
to your future career

233
00:19:51,247 --> 00:19:52,808
over coming here on time?

234
00:19:52,832 --> 00:19:54,752
- Excuse...
- You had me waiting for ten minutes!

235
00:19:55,209 --> 00:19:57,419
Fine! Okay. I'm sorry.

236
00:20:05,469 --> 00:20:06,679
There's our target.

237
00:20:28,534 --> 00:20:30,202
Ma'am, sir, are you staying here?

238
00:20:32,413 --> 00:20:35,124
Sir, don't you remember me?

239
00:20:36,208 --> 00:20:38,460
Ah, you're ma'am Rosetta's friend?

240
00:20:39,336 --> 00:20:41,898
You're the ones
who solved the case last week?

241
00:20:41,922 --> 00:20:43,275
Yes, that was us.

242
00:20:43,299 --> 00:20:46,177
Actually, I'm just visiting my friend again.

243
00:20:46,594 --> 00:20:48,345
Alright, ma'am. Just log in.

244
00:21:04,737 --> 00:21:06,572
Third floor, please?

245
00:21:28,802 --> 00:21:32,806
We need to figure out a way to get in
and grab Charles' phone.

246
00:21:33,140 --> 00:21:35,684
What if we just wait for him
to come out again?

247
00:21:36,518 --> 00:21:40,856
Then just lockpick the door
so we can go inside.

248
00:21:54,453 --> 00:21:55,996
We might be waiting in vain.

249
00:21:57,248 --> 00:21:59,792
We're not sure if he'll come out again.

250
00:22:01,085 --> 00:22:03,087
Lorelei, we have to do something.

251
00:22:10,052 --> 00:22:11,345
Charles just went live.

252
00:22:14,181 --> 00:22:17,142
Hi, guys! So today, it's ramen time!

253
00:22:17,643 --> 00:22:20,020
Not the instant kind,

254
00:22:20,312 --> 00:22:21,981
I had real ramen delivered.

255
00:22:22,648 --> 00:22:24,775
This guy surely is full of himself.

256
00:22:25,317 --> 00:22:28,696
Imagine, live streaming on your own
while eating.

257
00:22:29,947 --> 00:22:31,490
Talk about narcissism.

258
00:22:31,824 --> 00:22:35,411
At least we know
that he's alone in the room.

259
00:22:35,494 --> 00:22:38,580
And we know where to get his phone.

260
00:22:51,218 --> 00:22:52,469
We can't wait for him.

261
00:22:54,179 --> 00:22:56,098
We'll make him come out of his hole.

262
00:22:57,683 --> 00:22:59,518
Wait! Where are you going?

263
00:23:09,695 --> 00:23:12,489
What was that? Come on, go outside!

264
00:23:52,488 --> 00:23:53,947
He left his phone!

265
00:23:54,323 --> 00:23:55,949
He's still on a live stream.

266
00:23:58,160 --> 00:23:59,160
Great!

267
00:23:59,411 --> 00:24:01,205
I'll get what we need from the room.

268
00:24:02,164 --> 00:24:03,415
Keep an eye out for me.

269
00:24:04,208 --> 00:24:05,208
What?

270
00:24:35,864 --> 00:24:37,116
Affirmative.

271
00:24:59,012 --> 00:25:01,932
Fire! Good thing there's no fire!

272
00:25:02,224 --> 00:25:05,286
What's wrong with you?
Watch where you're going. Idiot.

273
00:25:05,310 --> 00:25:07,771
Sorry, I didn't notice you.

274
00:25:11,483 --> 00:25:13,652
Your sorry means nothing,
you already hit me.

275
00:25:15,362 --> 00:25:17,114
Good thing you're pretty.

276
00:25:26,442 --> 00:25:28,986
All the compromising photos
and files are here.

277
00:25:29,585 --> 00:25:33,922
I turned off the phone's tracking device,
so he can't locate it.

278
00:25:37,801 --> 00:25:39,219
We'll handle this

279
00:25:39,744 --> 00:25:42,330
including whatever sanction
we decide to give him.

280
00:25:51,273 --> 00:25:52,858
Do you need anything else?

281
00:25:56,945 --> 00:26:01,366
Maybe it's too much to expect
a thank you from you.

282
00:26:02,075 --> 00:26:03,827
You can't even say the magic word.

283
00:26:07,539 --> 00:26:08,665
Loki

284
00:26:09,833 --> 00:26:14,004
this is simply your payment for us
not dissolving your club.

285
00:26:15,839 --> 00:26:19,718
As I said,
do us this favor and we're even.

286
00:26:21,303 --> 00:26:22,429
Is that clear?

287
00:26:24,848 --> 00:26:26,767
Now that our debt is settled,

288
00:26:27,726 --> 00:26:29,228
you can stay away from us.

289
00:26:30,896 --> 00:26:31,939
We

290
00:26:32,814 --> 00:26:34,733
definitely don't enjoy your company!

291
00:26:35,984 --> 00:26:40,864
Well, unfortunately, I'm quite sure
that we will be crossing paths again.

292
00:26:41,198 --> 00:26:43,586
Even if we don't want to.

293
00:27:09,101 --> 00:27:11,770
You don't need to include this case
in the Chronicles.

294
00:27:13,146 --> 00:27:14,147
Got it.

295
00:27:15,816 --> 00:27:17,734
Just remember what I told you
about Luthor.

296
00:27:21,947 --> 00:27:24,783
Don't get involved with him
as much as possible.

297
00:27:29,037 --> 00:27:30,289
It's for your own good.

298
00:27:45,804 --> 00:27:48,307
Crazy what happened
at White Hostel yesterday, right?

299
00:27:52,436 --> 00:27:55,856
They're now investigating
who pressed the alarm.

300
00:27:58,817 --> 00:28:00,235
Hey, Lorelei.

301
00:28:03,030 --> 00:28:05,824
Go on, Rosetta. You should get to class.

302
00:28:09,703 --> 00:28:12,056
Congratulations on another case closed,

303
00:28:12,080 --> 00:28:15,167
though I heard that you stirred up
quite a scene at the hostel.

304
00:28:15,292 --> 00:28:17,002
What do you want now?

305
00:28:17,502 --> 00:28:20,464
Don't tell me
you've already fallen for him?

306
00:28:21,006 --> 00:28:22,633
How pitiful.

307
00:28:23,300 --> 00:28:26,237
Just because I help Loki
on investigations

308
00:28:26,261 --> 00:28:28,823
doesn't mean I have feelings for him.

309
00:28:28,847 --> 00:28:31,725
And one more thing,
it's none of your business.

310
00:28:32,059 --> 00:28:34,394
I thought you said
you'd stop bothering me.

311
00:28:35,270 --> 00:28:37,773
I did say
that I wouldn't bother you anymore.

312
00:28:38,148 --> 00:28:41,318
But that doesn't mean
we won't see each other again.

313
00:28:42,444 --> 00:28:43,987
So what do you really want?

314
00:28:44,279 --> 00:28:46,581
I'm just here to deliver a message.

315
00:28:47,407 --> 00:28:49,074
The vice president wants to meet you.

316
00:28:50,243 --> 00:28:52,036
Just remember
what I told you about Luthor.

317
00:28:53,455 --> 00:28:55,999
Don't get involved with him
as much as possible.

318
00:28:57,167 --> 00:28:58,251
Why?

319
00:28:58,752 --> 00:29:01,088
Aren't you interested
to know more about him?

320
00:29:02,214 --> 00:29:05,133
Don't you wanna know
why Loki hates him so much?

321
00:29:07,219 --> 00:29:10,722
Just be at the cafeteria later at 8 p.m.
if you want to meet him.

322
00:29:10,889 --> 00:29:11,889
Okay?

323
00:29:20,315 --> 00:29:22,377
Madonna, we're leaving.

324
00:29:22,401 --> 00:29:23,694
Aren't you coming?

325
00:29:24,236 --> 00:29:28,073
I'll go later. I still need to memorize this.

326
00:29:28,365 --> 00:29:30,492
You're taking that too seriously.

327
00:29:31,159 --> 00:29:32,345
I have to.

328
00:29:32,369 --> 00:29:34,996
I want to get the lead role
in the auditions.

329
00:29:35,247 --> 00:29:38,500
You know Jamie's
the theater club moderator's favorite.

330
00:29:39,876 --> 00:29:41,169
For now.

331
00:29:41,586 --> 00:29:44,089
But once they see how good I am,

332
00:29:44,297 --> 00:29:47,718
I'm sure Jamie's crown will be mine.

333
00:29:48,343 --> 00:29:50,804
Okay, Madonna. Good luck!

334
00:29:50,971 --> 00:29:52,264
We're going ahead, okay?

335
00:29:52,764 --> 00:29:54,117
Alright, go!

336
00:29:54,141 --> 00:29:55,952
Good luck, girl. You can do it!

337
00:29:55,976 --> 00:29:58,705
- You can definitely do it!
- Thank you! Thank you, guys!

338
00:29:58,729 --> 00:29:59,956
Make sure you watch, okay?

339
00:29:59,980 --> 00:30:02,041
- Yes. Of course!
- Of course, girl!

340
00:30:02,065 --> 00:30:03,126
Do your best!

341
00:30:03,150 --> 00:30:04,860
- Of course!
- Bye!

342
00:30:05,402 --> 00:30:06,945
Thank you!

343
00:30:07,320 --> 00:30:08,822
That one's all yours!

344
00:30:09,197 --> 00:30:12,200
I know! Come on, go.

345
00:30:47,486 --> 00:30:48,779
Hello, Lorelei.

346
00:30:49,404 --> 00:30:50,697
Hello, Luthor.

347
00:30:54,075 --> 00:30:55,075
Please…

348
00:30:55,535 --> 00:30:56,535
Sit.

349
00:31:13,470 --> 00:31:15,180
Thank you for meeting me this late.

350
00:31:15,555 --> 00:31:17,074
The cafeteria should be closed

351
00:31:17,098 --> 00:31:19,726
but I pulled some strings,
so we could have our meeting here.

352
00:31:22,604 --> 00:31:24,940
Are you sure
you don't want some tea or coffee?

353
00:31:25,857 --> 00:31:27,651
I still have a lot to do.

354
00:31:28,068 --> 00:31:29,402
Can we make this quick?

355
00:31:30,195 --> 00:31:31,321
Very well.

356
00:31:32,697 --> 00:31:34,407
I'm sorry for having you abducted.

357
00:31:34,658 --> 00:31:36,344
We had to resort to such methods

358
00:31:36,368 --> 00:31:40,455
since you refused to leave the club
that my brother is so fond of.

359
00:31:41,081 --> 00:31:42,934
We also wanted to test his resolve

360
00:31:42,958 --> 00:31:46,503
to see if he would come to your rescue
if you would be put in any danger.

361
00:31:49,714 --> 00:31:51,258
So Loki was right.

362
00:31:51,967 --> 00:31:53,927
You're the mastermind.

363
00:31:55,554 --> 00:31:56,596
Tell me,

364
00:31:56,888 --> 00:32:00,267
why are you forcing me
to leave the Q.E.D. Club?

365
00:32:01,393 --> 00:32:02,644
What's going on?

366
00:32:03,436 --> 00:32:05,564
Why are you so obsessed with it?

367
00:32:05,981 --> 00:32:09,234
Maggie must have told you repeatedly
that she wants to help you.

368
00:32:10,110 --> 00:32:11,319
The truth is

369
00:32:12,946 --> 00:32:14,590
we are just trying to protect you

370
00:32:14,614 --> 00:32:18,201
from any danger that might come
with your association with my brother.

371
00:32:19,619 --> 00:32:21,329
You know Rhea, right?

372
00:32:22,080 --> 00:32:24,374
And you know what happened to her.

373
00:32:25,667 --> 00:32:26,668
Yes.

374
00:32:27,377 --> 00:32:28,712
Loki said

375
00:32:29,379 --> 00:32:30,714
she was killed

376
00:32:31,214 --> 00:32:33,425
by someone known only as "M."

377
00:32:34,175 --> 00:32:36,469
And why would they kill an innocent girl?

378
00:32:40,015 --> 00:32:42,809
Because he was close to Loki.

379
00:32:45,520 --> 00:32:48,815
Every collision
has collateral damage, Lorelei.

380
00:32:50,275 --> 00:32:51,294
More than half a year ago,

381
00:32:51,318 --> 00:32:55,405
my brother investigated several cases
that connected all to one person…

382
00:32:55,947 --> 00:32:57,115
Only known as "M."

383
00:32:58,199 --> 00:33:01,137
And this elusive M seemingly struck back,

384
00:33:01,161 --> 00:33:03,830
by killing my brother's only friend.

385
00:33:04,664 --> 00:33:07,334
Rhea became that collateral damage.

386
00:33:09,169 --> 00:33:10,170
So…

387
00:33:11,129 --> 00:33:13,965
What does that have to do
with you kidnapping me?

388
00:33:14,007 --> 00:33:15,884
That M is still active.

389
00:33:16,801 --> 00:33:20,263
And you,
by being Loki's closest person…

390
00:33:21,806 --> 00:33:23,808
Could be the next collateral damage.

391
00:33:25,602 --> 00:33:27,187
We are trying to prevent that.

392
00:33:27,896 --> 00:33:31,191
I personally ask Maggie
to persuade you to leave the club.

393
00:33:32,108 --> 00:33:33,548
But it seems like you don't want to.

394
00:33:35,862 --> 00:33:39,115
Looks like you're willing
to take the risk for Loki.

395
00:33:40,742 --> 00:33:41,826
I wonder why.

396
00:33:43,036 --> 00:33:44,036
Well,

397
00:33:44,788 --> 00:33:47,499
if I end up as collateral damage,

398
00:33:48,375 --> 00:33:49,626
don't you think,

399
00:33:50,126 --> 00:33:54,547
I should be ready
for whatever happens to me,

400
00:33:55,340 --> 00:33:56,383
right?

401
00:33:59,094 --> 00:34:01,179
Loki loves mysteries,

402
00:34:03,264 --> 00:34:06,685
and you are a mystery to him, Lorelei.

403
00:34:07,936 --> 00:34:09,688
He doesn't see you as a person.

404
00:34:10,939 --> 00:34:14,025
He sees you as a puzzle
that he needs to solve.

405
00:34:15,568 --> 00:34:17,129
I was thinking that it's possible

406
00:34:17,153 --> 00:34:20,198
that the both of you
are seeking to escape a tragic past.

407
00:34:21,825 --> 00:34:26,871
See, Loki lost someone important
in his life.

408
00:34:28,081 --> 00:34:30,166
And I was wondering, what about you?

409
00:34:30,709 --> 00:34:32,627
What happened in your previous school?

410
00:34:35,171 --> 00:34:36,840
Is there anything that happened?

411
00:34:41,261 --> 00:34:44,931
I can see why your brother
gets annoyed with you.

412
00:34:48,059 --> 00:34:50,353
You think you know better than any of us.

413
00:34:51,896 --> 00:34:52,981
So what?

414
00:34:54,274 --> 00:34:55,525
You think that…

415
00:34:56,026 --> 00:35:00,655
You can control all of our decisions
and fix our actions

416
00:35:00,697 --> 00:35:02,699
that you deem as mistakes.

417
00:35:05,285 --> 00:35:08,538
Lorelei, I can assure you
that is not my intention.

418
00:35:10,957 --> 00:35:12,167
If you say so.

419
00:35:13,001 --> 00:35:14,669
Now if you'll excuse me,

420
00:35:15,253 --> 00:35:16,588
I have to get going.

421
00:35:21,051 --> 00:35:22,761
One more thing, Lorelei…

422
00:35:24,429 --> 00:35:25,889
This is just a hunch.

423
00:35:27,140 --> 00:35:29,976
But Loki might use you as a bait

424
00:35:30,060 --> 00:35:31,436
to lure out M.

425
00:35:33,438 --> 00:35:35,190
Just like cheese on a mouse trap.

426
00:35:36,775 --> 00:35:38,151
I hope I'm wrong.

427
00:36:03,051 --> 00:36:05,261
Hey! You guys are OA!

428
00:36:05,553 --> 00:36:07,097
Seriously…

429
00:36:07,597 --> 00:36:09,516
You're just messing with me.

430
00:36:10,308 --> 00:36:12,060
Is anyone around?

431
00:36:13,520 --> 00:36:14,789
These guys...

432
00:36:14,813 --> 00:36:16,523
OA! OA!

433
00:36:17,899 --> 00:36:19,418
Tell me the truth!

434
00:36:19,442 --> 00:36:21,986
Am I no longer the one
your heart beats for?

435
00:36:47,011 --> 00:36:48,888
Tell me the truth.

436
00:36:50,682 --> 00:36:53,351
Am I no longer the one
your heart beats for?

437
00:36:54,853 --> 00:36:57,188
Is there someone else who owns you now?

438
00:36:59,899 --> 00:37:01,377
If that's the case,

439
00:37:01,401 --> 00:37:03,278
I promise you

440
00:37:05,155 --> 00:37:07,240
you'll never see me again.

441
00:37:07,824 --> 00:37:11,953
You'll never see me again
for the rest of your life!

442
00:37:13,121 --> 00:37:14,497
Goodbye.

443
00:37:24,048 --> 00:37:25,133
Hello?

444
00:37:26,259 --> 00:37:27,802
Who's that?

445
00:37:28,845 --> 00:37:31,723
Hey, you guys again! So OA!

446
00:37:35,852 --> 00:37:38,581
Now you're even scaring
me. You guys, seriously!

447
00:37:38,605 --> 00:37:41,524
Enough with the prank!
Enough with the prank!

448
00:37:50,200 --> 00:37:51,201
Loki?

449
00:37:51,910 --> 00:37:53,328
Is that you?

450
00:37:57,790 --> 00:37:59,250
What are you doing here?

451
00:37:59,792 --> 00:38:03,504
I decided to, you know,
finish some work at the Q.E.D. Club.

452
00:38:03,963 --> 00:38:06,507
And decided to wait for you.

453
00:38:06,925 --> 00:38:07,902
Going home?

454
00:38:07,926 --> 00:38:08,926
Mm-hmm.

455
00:38:11,554 --> 00:38:12,722
Something wrong?

456
00:38:16,309 --> 00:38:19,896
Seems like your mind's roaming
around the cosmic space.

457
00:38:23,358 --> 00:38:25,068
Can I ask something?

458
00:38:25,902 --> 00:38:27,195
Yeah, sure.

459
00:38:28,696 --> 00:38:31,950
I hope it's a life-changing question.

460
00:38:42,710 --> 00:38:44,254
Are you hungry?

461
00:38:47,257 --> 00:38:48,549
That's it?

462
00:38:49,968 --> 00:38:51,094
No...

463
00:38:52,178 --> 00:38:53,513
No hypothetical,

464
00:38:53,888 --> 00:38:55,223
existential,

465
00:38:55,723 --> 00:38:57,934
or metaphysical query?

466
00:38:59,018 --> 00:39:00,228
Nothing.

467
00:39:01,187 --> 00:39:03,624
Because I've been hungry for a while now.

468
00:39:03,648 --> 00:39:05,024
I was just wondering.

469
00:39:06,734 --> 00:39:07,986
We can buy food.

470
00:39:10,780 --> 00:39:11,864
Okay.

471
00:39:14,450 --> 00:39:15,535
Yup.

472
00:39:16,452 --> 00:39:17,912
This is just a hunch.

473
00:39:18,538 --> 00:39:21,249
Loki might use you as bait to lure out M.

474
00:39:21,958 --> 00:39:23,167
I hope I'm wrong.

475
00:39:36,055 --> 00:39:37,265
How's it going?

476
00:39:38,766 --> 00:39:41,769
The OSA has decided
to suspend me for a week

477
00:39:42,020 --> 00:39:45,565
because of the commotion I caused
at the White Hostel the other day.

478
00:39:47,317 --> 00:39:48,693
But they took it back right away.

479
00:39:49,527 --> 00:39:52,572
My sibling worked some magic,
so the suspension was lifted.

480
00:39:52,613 --> 00:39:53,948
It's a good thing.

481
00:39:54,991 --> 00:39:58,911
I can't imagine the clubroom
if you get suspended.

482
00:39:59,912 --> 00:40:02,099
I won't be able to take clients,

483
00:40:02,123 --> 00:40:04,876
or solve cases by myself.

484
00:40:05,835 --> 00:40:07,479
Even if I get suspended,

485
00:40:07,503 --> 00:40:10,173
I still be in the clubroom no matter what.

486
00:40:11,132 --> 00:40:13,009
Classes are the only thing I can't go to.

487
00:40:13,343 --> 00:40:14,844
But I can still manage…

488
00:40:15,345 --> 00:40:16,596
Club affairs.

489
00:40:17,388 --> 00:40:18,848
And to be frank

490
00:40:19,474 --> 00:40:21,059
I prefer being suspended.

491
00:40:22,101 --> 00:40:26,428
So that I wouldn't have to pretend
to listen to my boring instructors.

492
00:40:27,940 --> 00:40:32,715
I hope, at least,
you learned something from what happened.

493
00:40:33,404 --> 00:40:36,741
Also, I think
you should thank your brother.

494
00:40:37,200 --> 00:40:38,844
If it weren't for him,

495
00:40:38,868 --> 00:40:40,948
you probably wouldn't have been able
to attend class.

496
00:40:41,079 --> 00:40:42,246
Why should I?

497
00:40:43,539 --> 00:40:47,168
The student council,
through him, asked for our help.

498
00:40:47,502 --> 00:40:49,992
It's their duty to cover our asses!

499
00:40:50,505 --> 00:40:52,048
They should be the one thanking us,

500
00:40:52,423 --> 00:40:53,883
not the other way around.

501
00:41:08,606 --> 00:41:09,792
By the way,

502
00:41:09,816 --> 00:41:13,152
I found out the one being blackmailed
is a student council officer.

503
00:41:13,486 --> 00:41:14,654
Really?

504
00:41:17,907 --> 00:41:19,492
You'll be surprised to know…

505
00:41:20,326 --> 00:41:22,471
That Charles Meliton is connected

506
00:41:22,495 --> 00:41:24,872
to a problem brought to us
by another client.

507
00:41:26,040 --> 00:41:27,434
Do you remember that poor girl

508
00:41:27,458 --> 00:41:30,211
who wore skirt
some inches abover her knees?

509
00:41:30,753 --> 00:41:32,523
Madonna Barcelon?

510
00:41:32,547 --> 00:41:34,674
The one betrayed by her friend?

511
00:41:35,133 --> 00:41:38,570
Maybe they're just jealous of my beauty?

512
00:41:38,594 --> 00:41:41,139
Madonna, you go, girl!

513
00:41:41,597 --> 00:41:42,682
That one.

514
00:41:43,182 --> 00:41:45,560
How are the two cases connected?

515
00:41:47,186 --> 00:41:50,314
He was the one
who blackmailed Malena's friend,

516
00:41:51,190 --> 00:41:55,486
to feed him embarrassing information
to our ex-client.

517
00:41:56,946 --> 00:41:59,157
You mean Madonna, right?

518
00:41:59,532 --> 00:42:03,429
Apparently, someone ordered him
to find dirt on the student council

519
00:42:03,453 --> 00:42:06,247
in exchange of embarasssing photos.

520
00:42:07,248 --> 00:42:09,125
So, there's a third party involved?

521
00:42:09,750 --> 00:42:10,877
Who?

522
00:42:11,711 --> 00:42:15,298
He doesn't know the identity
of this anonymous source.

523
00:42:16,591 --> 00:42:18,676
They only communicate online,

524
00:42:20,011 --> 00:42:23,014
and the account they use is a dummy email.

525
00:42:25,099 --> 00:42:26,601
Excuse me.

526
00:42:26,851 --> 00:42:29,455
Am I disturbing you?

527
00:42:29,479 --> 00:42:32,749
If you're busy, I'll just come back later.

528
00:42:32,773 --> 00:42:35,943
No, not really! Please, have a seat.

529
00:42:37,111 --> 00:42:40,990
Do you have a case to consult
or bring to us?

530
00:42:41,240 --> 00:42:43,367
How can we help you?

531
00:42:44,494 --> 00:42:46,287
I'm Geneva.

532
00:42:47,330 --> 00:42:49,558
My classmate is missing.

533
00:42:49,582 --> 00:42:54,378
I'm sure you know her,
since she's asked for your help before.

534
00:42:55,254 --> 00:42:58,567
Sorry, but we've already helped a lot.

535
00:42:58,591 --> 00:43:00,551
Who are you talking about?

536
00:43:01,260 --> 00:43:03,054
It's Madonna Barcelon.

537
00:43:04,972 --> 00:43:07,016
Madonna and I are dormmates.

538
00:43:07,725 --> 00:43:10,186
She didn't go home last night.

539
00:43:10,645 --> 00:43:14,899
I even went to the theater
because I knew she'd be practicing there.

540
00:43:15,483 --> 00:43:17,944
I even went back to get my dorm keys…

541
00:43:20,821 --> 00:43:22,698
Because I forgot.

542
00:43:24,408 --> 00:43:27,537
She said she'd just be home late.

543
00:43:28,996 --> 00:43:31,415
But she never made it home.

544
00:43:31,958 --> 00:43:34,835
She didn't even call or text me.

545
00:43:38,798 --> 00:43:43,469
Well, how can you conclude
that she's missing based on that?

546
00:43:43,886 --> 00:43:46,347
Maybe she went to one of her many suitors.

547
00:43:47,515 --> 00:43:49,767
But she didn't go to class earlier.

548
00:43:50,601 --> 00:43:55,231
I called her phone several times,
but it's out of coverage area.

549
00:43:56,190 --> 00:43:59,628
I asked the guys she might've gone to,

550
00:43:59,652 --> 00:44:02,613
but Madonna didn't contact any of them.

551
00:44:03,489 --> 00:44:06,492
Didn't anyone actually
see her leave campus?

552
00:44:08,327 --> 00:44:12,933
I asked the guards and showed her photo

553
00:44:12,957 --> 00:44:16,085
if they noticed Madonna leaving,

554
00:44:16,419 --> 00:44:19,255
but they didn't see her.

555
00:44:20,840 --> 00:44:23,968
I already reported everything
to campus police.

556
00:44:25,177 --> 00:44:28,907
But I think it'll take a
while to solve the case

557
00:44:28,931 --> 00:44:31,183
because they've got a lot of work.

558
00:44:31,851 --> 00:44:35,980
That's why I decided to come to you.

559
00:44:38,566 --> 00:44:39,609
Well

560
00:44:41,527 --> 00:44:43,321
I'm not interested in this one.

561
00:44:45,156 --> 00:44:48,200
This case is not worth our time.

562
00:44:49,118 --> 00:44:51,329
Once it's confirmed that she's missing,

563
00:44:52,079 --> 00:44:55,183
you can return to us
or leave this case to the campus police.

564
00:44:55,207 --> 00:44:56,334
Loki!

565
00:44:58,419 --> 00:45:02,131
Are you sure
Madonna didn't go anywhere else?

566
00:45:02,840 --> 00:45:05,068
She always tells me

567
00:45:05,092 --> 00:45:07,720
or texts me when she's going somewhere.

568
00:45:08,137 --> 00:45:12,141
But this time, she didn't say anything
or even give a sign.

569
00:45:13,142 --> 00:45:16,812
Until it is proven
that your friend is indeed missing,

570
00:45:17,855 --> 00:45:19,690
this case is not worth our time.

571
00:45:20,316 --> 00:45:24,820
If you think Madonna's not really missing,
let's prove it to Geneva.

572
00:45:25,154 --> 00:45:27,281
Isn't that what Q.E.D. is all about?

573
00:45:27,615 --> 00:45:30,034
Helping people! Right?

574
00:45:31,327 --> 00:45:32,328
Fine!

575
00:45:32,536 --> 00:45:34,705
We'll prove that your friend isn't missing

576
00:45:35,331 --> 00:45:37,375
and she shouldn't be worried about her.

577
00:45:38,542 --> 00:45:41,087
I'm going to call the
campus security office.

578
00:45:41,671 --> 00:45:43,774
They owe me big time,

579
00:45:43,798 --> 00:45:49,428
so I'm sure they'll let me check
yesterday's footage.

580
00:45:51,555 --> 00:45:54,266
We'll see Madonna leave school,

581
00:45:54,517 --> 00:45:56,060
and check if she's with someone.

582
00:46:04,944 --> 00:46:07,071
What time did you last see her on campus?

583
00:46:07,738 --> 00:46:10,658
Around quarter to 5?

584
00:46:12,326 --> 00:46:14,930
There's only one campus exit and entrance,

585
00:46:14,954 --> 00:46:18,040
so we could immediately see if she left.

586
00:46:30,678 --> 00:46:32,179
Can we check that again?

587
00:46:36,600 --> 00:46:40,688
Told you, she didn't leave the campus.

588
00:46:42,148 --> 00:46:45,943
Isn't there any other secret exit
Madonna could've used?

589
00:46:46,402 --> 00:46:47,695
Nothing, ma'am.

590
00:46:49,155 --> 00:46:50,698
Is he still the one on duty?

591
00:46:51,699 --> 00:46:53,826
Yes, sir. It's still Muldong.

592
00:46:55,494 --> 00:46:57,705
This is a thrilling case after all!

593
00:46:58,664 --> 00:47:00,708
If Madonna really didn't leave,

594
00:47:01,041 --> 00:47:03,294
she must still be on campus.

595
00:47:03,961 --> 00:47:05,921
She could've been slain
in one of the rooms.

596
00:47:06,255 --> 00:47:10,068
And this might be a missing corpse case.

597
00:47:10,092 --> 00:47:11,385
Loki, come on!

598
00:47:12,845 --> 00:47:15,765
We're going to find her. Okay?

599
00:47:19,101 --> 00:47:20,978
Hello, sir?

600
00:47:22,354 --> 00:47:25,125
I'm the one who asked you
earlier this morning.

601
00:47:25,149 --> 00:47:29,779
I just want to confirm,
did you really not see my friend?

602
00:47:32,615 --> 00:47:36,285
There's no way I'd forget this,
she's gorgeous.

603
00:47:36,786 --> 00:47:39,413
I have a sharp memory,
I'll recognize her right away.

604
00:47:42,291 --> 00:47:44,668
Are missing students a thing now?

605
00:47:45,878 --> 00:47:48,255
Are there any other missing students?

606
00:47:48,464 --> 00:47:49,507
Yes.

607
00:47:50,591 --> 00:47:53,570
The campus police officers came here.

608
00:47:53,594 --> 00:47:58,224
They're asking if I saw any students,
two girls.

609
00:47:58,599 --> 00:48:02,686
They're asking if I saw them
leave the building on Monday and Tuesday.

610
00:48:02,853 --> 00:48:06,649
I saw them go in,
but I didn't see them come out.

611
00:48:07,316 --> 00:48:09,568
Too bad, they were actually really nice.

612
00:48:09,985 --> 00:48:11,946
I hope their parents find them soon.

613
00:48:13,322 --> 00:48:14,740
I have some questions.

614
00:48:15,449 --> 00:48:16,450
First,

615
00:48:17,201 --> 00:48:19,912
we saw you leave your desk at 7 p.m.

616
00:48:20,454 --> 00:48:22,206
Where did you go at that time?

617
00:48:24,959 --> 00:48:26,895
That's part of our job.

618
00:48:26,919 --> 00:48:29,088
To double-check the students,

619
00:48:29,588 --> 00:48:30,923
if they've already left.

620
00:48:31,632 --> 00:48:33,944
We also check every room

621
00:48:33,968 --> 00:48:36,470
to see if there were any students left.

622
00:48:36,846 --> 00:48:38,681
I checked all the floors.

623
00:48:41,141 --> 00:48:42,893
On the 5th floor, where the theater is…

624
00:48:43,269 --> 00:48:45,104
Did you notice anything unusual?

625
00:48:46,605 --> 00:48:47,857
Not really.

626
00:48:49,608 --> 00:48:51,068
Do you always do rounds?

627
00:48:51,944 --> 00:48:54,238
Since I was on duty Sunday, yes.

628
00:48:55,573 --> 00:48:58,576
Didn't you notice anything unusual
on any of the floors?

629
00:49:01,287 --> 00:49:03,747
On one room on the 4th floor,

630
00:49:04,039 --> 00:49:05,624
the door won't stay shut.

631
00:49:05,916 --> 00:49:08,878
No matter how I close it,
it keeps opening.

632
00:49:09,545 --> 00:49:12,590
And on the basement, by the anatomy room,

633
00:49:13,173 --> 00:49:15,009
there's always a foul smell.

634
00:49:15,676 --> 00:49:18,137
Sometimes, I feel like
there's someone there.

635
00:49:18,429 --> 00:49:21,015
But when I peek in, there's nothing.

636
00:49:21,891 --> 00:49:23,809
I didn't inspect it at all.

637
00:49:24,518 --> 00:49:29,148
Because I'm scared
I might see a real corpse.

638
00:49:33,569 --> 00:49:34,737
Thank you.

639
00:49:35,821 --> 00:49:36,864
Yeah.

640
00:49:39,325 --> 00:49:40,492
Thanks, chief.

641
00:49:43,329 --> 00:49:44,788
What did chief say?

642
00:49:45,956 --> 00:49:50,419
Apparently, they already know
about the missing female students' cases.

643
00:49:51,503 --> 00:49:53,088
But they still don't have a lead.

644
00:49:54,381 --> 00:49:59,678
The other girls missing are named
Mylene Canlas and Michelle De Guzman.

645
00:50:00,930 --> 00:50:03,617
They already searched
the campus a few days ago

646
00:50:03,641 --> 00:50:05,184
but they found no corpse

647
00:50:05,643 --> 00:50:09,647
or trace if either or both are dead.

648
00:50:11,315 --> 00:50:13,484
It doesn't look like a
kidnapping for ransom,

649
00:50:13,692 --> 00:50:16,320
because no one's contacting their parents.

650
00:50:17,738 --> 00:50:20,950
There's a high chance it's murder.

651
00:50:22,284 --> 00:50:24,078
But where could their bodies be?

652
00:50:25,955 --> 00:50:28,999
Could this be a case of serial killing?

653
00:50:29,917 --> 00:50:31,752
It seems like there's a pattern.

654
00:50:31,961 --> 00:50:35,506
Mylene, Michelle, Madonna.

655
00:50:36,507 --> 00:50:40,386
They all disappeared, like magic.

656
00:50:42,346 --> 00:50:44,682
You're probably right, Lorelei.

657
00:50:45,474 --> 00:50:46,660
The person behind these incidents

658
00:50:46,684 --> 00:50:48,811
must have used magic
to make them disappear.

659
00:50:49,728 --> 00:50:51,146
Are you serious?

660
00:50:51,271 --> 00:50:54,191
There's another case
that maybe connected to this one.

661
00:50:55,401 --> 00:50:57,653
Do you remember the chemistry lab case?

662
00:51:00,781 --> 00:51:02,491
According to Chief Estrada,

663
00:51:03,033 --> 00:51:06,286
the missing chemical compounds in the lab

664
00:51:06,370 --> 00:51:08,163
are Sodium Hydroxide.

665
00:51:09,331 --> 00:51:12,042
At first, I was clueless
as to why someone would steal them.

666
00:51:13,252 --> 00:51:18,048
Then I realized that it could make
the disappearance happen as if by magic.

667
00:51:21,218 --> 00:51:23,512
Sorry, I'm not good at chemistry.

668
00:51:23,762 --> 00:51:25,139
What's that for?

669
00:51:27,099 --> 00:51:28,809
It's used as a drain cleaner.

670
00:51:29,393 --> 00:51:31,454
You pour that chemical down the drain

671
00:51:31,478 --> 00:51:34,356
to remove human hair clogging the pipes.

672
00:51:35,399 --> 00:51:37,192
It can also be used to melt bodies.

673
00:51:37,735 --> 00:51:39,069
Human bodies.

674
00:51:42,239 --> 00:51:43,615
Give it a few hours

675
00:51:44,033 --> 00:51:45,743
and it will leave no trace

676
00:51:46,618 --> 00:51:48,037
except for teeth

677
00:51:48,746 --> 00:51:49,913
and nails.

678
00:51:54,835 --> 00:51:55,961
Now

679
00:51:56,920 --> 00:52:01,133
guess who might be
behind all these intertwined mysteries?

680
00:52:01,800 --> 00:52:03,403
Someone who asked Genesis

681
00:52:03,427 --> 00:52:06,305
to steal botttles of sodium hydroxide
from the lab.

682
00:52:07,222 --> 00:52:10,410
And someone who was disappointed
that Madonna Barcelon's image

683
00:52:10,434 --> 00:52:14,146
wasn't totally ruined by her dirty secret.

684
00:52:14,438 --> 00:52:18,275
Someone who decided to use a brutal
yet clean method

685
00:52:18,776 --> 00:52:22,613
to dispose of a person
who they deemed a nuisance.

686
00:52:23,530 --> 00:52:24,698
M?

687
00:52:26,867 --> 00:52:29,661
Judging by how almost flawless
these incidents are,

688
00:52:30,412 --> 00:52:32,748
only M could be the one behind it.

689
00:52:33,791 --> 00:52:35,918
But I don't believe in perfect crimes

690
00:52:36,043 --> 00:52:39,213
because those who commit them are humans.

691
00:52:41,381 --> 00:52:43,967
Prone to errors and imperfections.

692
00:52:45,052 --> 00:52:47,739
He might have committed
some mistakes along the way

693
00:52:47,763 --> 00:52:49,389
that would lead us to them.

694
00:52:50,432 --> 00:52:52,559
I'm thrilled to solve this case.

695
00:52:54,228 --> 00:52:55,771
And I realized something.

696
00:52:59,483 --> 00:53:01,527
He wants to send me a message,

697
00:53:02,277 --> 00:53:05,239
that's why all the victims' names
start with M.

698
00:53:08,450 --> 00:53:12,579
That M would do anything
just to get on my nerves.

699
00:53:13,330 --> 00:53:14,832
If it really is him,

700
00:53:15,707 --> 00:53:17,334
I hope we're not too late.

701
00:53:18,168 --> 00:53:21,588
I hope we can still find the missing ones.

702
00:53:25,843 --> 00:53:28,053
Loki, I'll go ahead.

703
00:53:28,762 --> 00:53:29,948
I still have class.

704
00:53:29,972 --> 00:53:33,475
Just text me if there are any new updates
about the case.

705
00:53:34,643 --> 00:53:37,271
How about you? Aren't you going to class?

706
00:53:39,189 --> 00:53:42,651
I'll probably skip them today
so I can work on this case.

707
00:54:20,022 --> 00:54:23,400
Mylene and Michelle
were last seen on campus around 5 p.m.

708
00:54:25,777 --> 00:54:29,364
Mylene was last seen in room 205
where her last class was.

709
00:54:35,120 --> 00:54:37,140
Michelle was last seen
in the English clubroom

710
00:54:37,164 --> 00:54:38,624
before she disappeared.

711
00:54:40,584 --> 00:54:43,295
Meanwhile, Madonna was in the auditorium.

712
00:54:44,421 --> 00:54:47,424
I went to every room
but there were no traces of blood.

713
00:54:49,509 --> 00:54:51,529
So, is this like Janine's case,

714
00:54:51,553 --> 00:54:55,182
where they knew the culprit
and went voluntarily?

715
00:55:03,899 --> 00:55:07,152
Unlikely.
They don't have a single common friend.

716
00:55:11,448 --> 00:55:16,012
How did the culprit move the victims
without anyone noticing?

717
00:55:16,036 --> 00:55:19,581
Maybe we should ask Chief Estrada
for help in the search.

718
00:55:24,336 --> 00:55:28,382
No. If M is involved,
I don't want to involve the police.

719
00:55:28,632 --> 00:55:30,259
M is mine.

720
00:55:32,928 --> 00:55:34,137
Excuse me?

721
00:55:34,471 --> 00:55:37,933
We have an activity going on.
Please give me that phone.

722
00:55:38,183 --> 00:55:40,703
Sorry, ma'am. It's important.

723
00:55:40,727 --> 00:55:42,896
You can have it back after class.

724
00:55:43,981 --> 00:55:45,148
Please?

725
00:55:57,327 --> 00:55:58,870
Loki, please pick up.

726
00:56:02,457 --> 00:56:04,626
Sorry! Sorry! I'm just in a hurry.

727
00:56:07,879 --> 00:56:09,506
Oh, come on.

728
00:56:13,677 --> 00:56:14,970
What's this?

729
00:56:16,805 --> 00:56:18,849
Pick up the phone. Come on.

730
00:56:45,042 --> 00:56:46,335
Loki, why...

731
00:56:49,463 --> 00:56:51,590
Oh, sorry.

732
00:56:58,764 --> 00:56:59,931
Wait,

733
00:57:00,891 --> 00:57:03,018
why do you seem familiar?

734
00:57:15,238 --> 00:57:16,823
John Bautista?

735
00:57:18,283 --> 00:57:20,345
John Bautista, secretary.

736
00:57:20,369 --> 00:57:22,579
- What did you do to Isaac, huh?
- John, believe me!

737
00:57:23,705 --> 00:57:26,083
But why are you dressed as a janitor?

738
00:57:45,977 --> 00:57:47,270
Help!

739
00:57:59,699 --> 00:58:01,493
Help!

740
00:59:55,315 --> 00:59:56,483
You?

741
00:59:56,858 --> 00:59:58,902
You're the one who abducted them?

742
00:59:59,444 --> 01:00:00,654
Yeah, it's me!

743
01:00:01,279 --> 01:00:02,948
And now it's your turn.

744
01:01:23,737 --> 01:01:26,990
Looks like we need to teach
that guy a lesson again.

745
01:01:27,282 --> 01:01:30,285
Let's see if he still won't learn from this.

746
01:01:33,079 --> 01:01:34,372
She's awake.

747
01:01:58,647 --> 01:02:00,374
I don't want to die yet!

748
01:02:00,398 --> 01:02:02,960
I want to achieve my dreams.

749
01:02:02,984 --> 01:02:06,738
I still want to get to know Loki
and myself.

750
01:02:07,197 --> 01:02:09,532
I admire your survival instincts,
for a woman.

751
01:02:16,831 --> 01:02:20,543
I only knew him as “M,” that's it.

752
01:02:20,919 --> 01:02:22,980
He's everywhere, Lorelei.

753
01:02:23,004 --> 01:02:26,651
He's got eyes and ears everywhere.

754
01:02:26,675 --> 01:02:30,571
Moriya! Moriarty!

755
01:02:30,595 --> 01:02:33,824
Moriya! Moriarty!

756
01:02:33,848 --> 01:02:37,018
Moriarity is a professor of Mathematics,

757
01:02:37,727 --> 01:02:39,622
known as "the Napoleon of crime."

758
01:02:39,646 --> 01:02:43,566
The mastermind
behind half of the evil in the world.
